716399f-a.text:
Three frame houses, 47-61 Audubon Avenue, east side, between 167th and 168th Streets.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 418.

716397f-b.title: ??Manhattan: Audubon Avenue - 167th Street (West)
716397f-b.text:
(1) Audubon Ave., east side from West 167th (right) to 168th (left) Streets, showing apartment houses at either corner. Between same are three 4-story frame houses, Nos. 47 to 51. This is a net of 2 views, No. 2 showing an eastward view to Amsterdam Ave. On the right.
July 30, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, different angle.
July 30, 1937
P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, from a different angle.
May 18th, 1940
P. L. Sperr.
